37:04.022 --> 37:08.860
- I DIDN'T KNOW ANYBODY
WROTE LONGHAND ANY MORE.

37:08.894 --> 37:11.463
- YEAH, COMPUTERS
ARE FINE FOR SOME THINGS,

37:11.497 --> 37:14.466
BUT WHEN I REALLY
WANT THE WORDS TO FLOW

37:14.500 --> 37:16.635
THROUGH MY MIND
AND OUT MY FINGERS,

37:16.668 --> 37:18.737
I FIND YE OLDE
TICONDEROGA NUMBER TWO

37:18.770 --> 37:22.741
BEATS THE HELL OUT
OF HIGH TECH ANY DAY.

37:22.774 --> 37:25.010
- THAT IS SO BEAUTIFUL.

37:25.043 --> 37:26.612
- WHAT IS?

37:26.645 --> 37:27.746
- WHAT YOU JUST SAID.

37:27.779 --> 37:30.749
THE WAY THE WORDS
JUST FLOWED.

37:30.782 --> 37:33.485
I WISH I COULD
BE THAT ELOQUENT.

37:33.519 --> 37:37.623
ESPECIALLY NOW,
WHEN I--

37:37.656 --> 37:40.959
I REALLY WANT
TO SAY I'M SORRY.

37:40.992 --> 37:43.395
- WHAT FOR?

37:43.429 --> 37:46.532
- FOR TAKING OFF.

37:46.565 --> 37:48.634
FOR--

37:48.667 --> 37:50.068
YOU THINK I COULD
GET A DRINK?

37:50.101 --> 37:54.673
- OH, YEAH, HELP YOURSELF.

37:54.706 --> 37:56.808
[opening fridge door]

37:56.842 --> 38:00.479
[opens bottle]

38:09.421 --> 38:11.690
- LOOK, I KNOW YOU DON'T
LIKE TO DWELL ON THE PAST.

38:11.723 --> 38:12.958
YOU KNOW, IT'S--

38:12.991 --> 38:17.463
IT'S OVER, IT'S GONE,
LET IT GO.

38:17.496 --> 38:20.466
BUT SOMETIMES,
IT WON'T LET YOU GO.

38:20.499 --> 38:24.736
LIKE WITH BRIAN.

38:24.770 --> 38:28.707
- WHAT ABOUT HIM?

38:28.740 --> 38:32.444
- WELL, I WASN'T
COMPLETELY HONEST WHEN I SAID

38:32.478 --> 38:35.947
IT DIDN'T MATTER
TO ME THAT

38:35.981 --> 38:40.085
YOU HAD HAD SEX WITH HIM,
IT DOES MATTER.

38:40.118 --> 38:42.087
- AND WHY'S THAT?

38:42.120 --> 38:45.323
- BECAUSE...

38:48.860 --> 38:52.898
BECAUSE I--I'VE ALWAYS
HAD CERTAIN FEELINGS FOR HIM.

38:52.931 --> 38:55.834
- WHAT KIND OF FEELINGS?

38:55.867 --> 38:57.736
- DIFFERENT KINDS.

38:57.769 --> 39:01.707
FRIENDSHIP FEELINGS.

39:01.740 --> 39:03.742
LOVE FEELINGS.

39:03.775 --> 39:07.012
- SEXUAL FEELINGS?

39:09.648 --> 39:12.751
- NOT THAT ANYTHING
EVER HAPPENED OR EVER WILL.

39:16.755 --> 39:19.057
BUT WHEN I FOUND OUT
THAT YOU AND HE--

39:19.090 --> 39:21.860
I JUST COULDN'T
STOP THINKING--

39:21.893 --> 39:26.865
- THAT I KNEW HIM...

39:26.898 --> 39:29.768
IN A WAY YOU DON'T.

39:29.801 --> 39:33.004
- AND HE KNOWS YOU
IN A WAY THAT I DO.

39:33.038 --> 39:35.641
- THANK YOU
FOR TELLING ME.

39:35.674 --> 39:38.644
- I HAD TO.
I LOVE YOU.

39:42.581 --> 39:44.483
- AND IT'S OKAY
THAT YOU LOVE HIM.

39:44.516 --> 39:46.618
- IT IS?
- UH-HUH.

39:46.652 --> 39:48.487
MICHAEL, WE'VE KNOWN
EACH OTHER FOR--

39:48.520 --> 39:50.689
HOW LONG, A FEW MONTHS?

39:50.722 --> 39:52.624
YOU HAD A LIFE
BEFORE I CAME ALONG.

39:52.658 --> 39:54.493
SO DID I.

39:54.526 --> 39:58.497
INCLUDING PEOPLE WE'VE LOVED,
THAT WE'RE STILL IN LOVE WITH.

39:58.530 --> 40:02.568
BUT THAT DOESN'T MEAN
WE CAN'T LOVE EACH OTHER.

40:25.491 --> 40:28.226
WHAT?

40:28.259 --> 40:31.630
- NOTHING.

40:36.267 --> 40:39.505
[approaching footsteps]

40:42.708 --> 40:44.242
- DEBBIE?

40:44.275 --> 40:46.011
WHY DON'T YOU
COME SIT DOWN.

40:46.044 --> 40:47.879
- THE RIGATONI'S
GETTING COLD.

40:47.913 --> 40:49.815
- YOU GO AHEAD,
I'M NOT HUNGRY.

40:49.848 --> 40:52.083
- HOW ABOUT A LITTLE WINE
TO CELEBRATE?

40:52.117 --> 40:54.553
- CELEBRATE WHAT?
- YOU GOT WHAT YOU WANTED.

40:54.586 --> 40:56.221
[doorbell chimes]

40:56.254 --> 40:57.956
YOU FOUND OUT HIS NAME.

40:57.989 --> 40:59.825
- SOMETHING EVEN
THE POLICE COULDN'T DO.

40:59.858 --> 41:01.760
- YEAH, THEY STILL
DON'T KNOW WHO HIS FAMILY IS

41:01.793 --> 41:04.763
OR WHO DID IT.

41:15.173 --> 41:17.743
